cs.NI, cs.MM, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on enhancing video services in next generation mobile networks using software-defined mobile networks, in-network caching, and mobile edge computing. This falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video streaming and video quality, which is a key aspect of multimedia research.
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper discusses the use of mobile edge computing to enhance video services, which involves distributed computing and processing.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper formulates an optimization problem to maximize the mean measurement of video quality, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with traffic engineering, bandwidth provisioning, and paths selection, which are related to information theory and communication systems.
